头阵列。对于中端智能手机来说，不同寻常的是，传感器可能包括长焦镜头。据称，Galaxy S23 FE 的屏幕尺寸约为 6.4 英寸，配备 120Hz AMOLED 面板和屏下指纹识别器。 </p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><div id="fb392889c5024d28a9fef1fa86e191c7"><blockquote class="twitter-tweet"><p dir="ltr" lang="en">早上好<a href="https://twitter.com/hashtag/FutureSquad?src=hash&amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">#FutureSquad</a> ！这是您第一次看到备受期待的<a href="https://twitter.com/hashtag/Samsung?src=hash&amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">#Samsung</a> <a href="https://twitter.com/hashtag/GalaxyS23FE?src=hash&amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">#GalaxyS23FE</a> ！ （360°视频+华丽的5K渲染+尺寸）<br><br>代表<a href="https://twitter.com/Smartprix?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">@Smartprix</a> 👉🏻 <a href="https://t.co/QTOJYYKBm8">https://t.co/QTOJYYKBm8</a> <a href="https://t.co/SgrDoFai7N">pic.twitter.com/SgrDoFai7N</a></p> — Steve H.McFly (@OnLeaks) <a href="https://twitter.com/OnLeaks/status/1673937715623079938?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">2023 年 6 月 28 日</a></blockquote></div><p>目前关于内部细节还不太清楚，因为<ins><a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.theverge.com/2023/6/28/23776731/we-could-be-getting-a-samsung-galaxy-s23-fe-this-year"><em>边缘</em></a></ins>笔记。有传言指出，从 2022 年起，部分市场的 Galaxy S23 FE 将运行在 Snapdragon 8 Plus Gen 1 芯片组上，而其他市场则将运行 Exynos 2200。它可以有 6GB 和 8GB RAM 选项以及 128GB 或 256GB 存储空间。</p><p> Hemmerstoffer 表示，Galaxy S23 FE 预计将于 2023 年底上市。我们可能也不必等待太久才能找到答案，因为三星将举办今年的第二次 Unpacked 活动<ins><a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/samsung-will-focus-on-foldables-in-its-upcoming-july-unpacked-event-064922443.html">在七月</a></ins>。 </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/b900c8f0-15be-11ee-bebf-5102b5148255" style="height:1440px;width:2560px;" alt="三星 Galaxy S23 FE 智能手机的正面和背面渲染。" data-uuid="fd1a9f5d-c02e-34d6-84b5-2c6a444d8247"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">史蒂夫·赫默斯托弗/Smartprix</div></figure><p></p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/a-samsung-galaxy-s23-fe-may-be-on-the-way-later-this-year-143559312.html?src=rss ]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/a-samsung-galaxy-s23-fe-may-be-on-the-way-later-this-year-143559312.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> bb5d9fee-2730-44c2-940c-83c75b7d9657</guid><dc:creator>克里斯·霍尔特</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Wed, 28 Jun 2023 14:35:59 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1687962306</ingested><modified> 2023-06-28T14:25:09+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Consumer Discretionary]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Kris Holt]]></category><media:content height="1333" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-02/38dcaed0-b391-11ed-badf-4523df37f3d5" width="2000"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="1333" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-02/38dcaed0-b391-11ed-badf-4523df37f3d5" width="2000"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Mat Smith / Engadget]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[A Samsung Galaxy S23+ smartphone is propped up in the middle of a conveyor belt with food.]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Samsung Galaxy S23+]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[OnePlus' first foldable phone will reportedly feature a 2K screen]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>一加可能是下一家进军可折叠手机领域的公司，它可能有一些方法可以脱颖而出。知名爆料者 OnLeaks 和<em>MySmartPrice</em> <a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.mysmartprice.com/gear/oneplus-fold-specifications-revealed-launch-exclusive/">声称</a>拥有 OnePlus Fold（又名 OnePlus V Fold）的规格，这是一款书本式可折叠设备，显然它将提供高端性能。据报道，它将采用 7.8 英寸“2K”折叠屏和 6.3 英寸外部显示屏（均为 120Hz），并配备快速的 Snapdragon 8 Gen 2 芯片以及 16GB RAM 和 256GB 存储空间。当手机打开时，你会在背面看到 48MP 普通和超广角摄像头、一个 64MP 长焦传感器、一个用于外部屏幕的 32MP 前置摄像头以及一个 20MP 自拍相机。</p><p> 4,800mAh 电池并不算特别，你必须满足于“仅仅”67W 快速有线充电，而不是<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/oneplus-11-review-price-release-date-cameras-150015371.html">OnePlus 11</a>的 100W。是的，尽管外形相对新颖，但该品牌标志性的警报滑块仍将脱颖而出。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>据传 OnePlus 将于今年 8 月推出 Fold，大约在三星非正式预计推出 Galaxy Z Fold 5 和<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/leaked-samsung-galaxy-z-flip-5-render-shows-a-bigger-cover-display-214020400.html">Galaxy Z Flip 5</a>一个月后。目前还没有关于定价的消息，但声称的硬件可能会使其价格昂贵。</p><p>可折叠手机类别仍然相对较小，北美人基本上必须在 Galaxy Z 系列、谷歌的<a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/google-pixel-fold-review-the-challenger-that-samsung-needs-specs-price-170003458.html">Pixel Fold</a>和摩托罗拉的<a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/moto-razr-review-finally-some-real-competition-for-samsungs-flip-foldables-203033514.html">Razr+</a>之间进行选择。不过，随着 OnePlus 进入这个领域，有迹象表明该领域正在升温。这对客户来说是个好消息，因为它可能会导致更激进的定价和此前甘于袖手旁观的新进入者。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/oneplus-first-foldable-phone-will-reportedly-feature-a-2k-screen-140426945.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/oneplus-first-foldable-phone-will-reportedly-feature-a-2k-screen-140426945.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 4445aa9a-d1f9-4a60-ab24-0a93ac88b0c5</guid><dc:creator>乔恩·芬加斯</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Wed, 28 Jun 2023 14:04:26 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1687962359</ingested><modified> 2023-06-28T14:26:02+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Consumer Discretionary]]></category><category><![CDATA[Handheld & Connected Devices]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Jon Fingas]]></category><media:content height="1254" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/974df6f0-15bf-11ee-a7f5-67882f47ac19" width="1895"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="1254" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/974df6f0-15bf-11ee-a7f5-67882f47ac19" width="1895"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[OnLeaks x SmartPrix]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[A leaked image of the OnePlus Fold in black seen against a dark grey background.]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[OnePlus Fold]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[The best Xbox games for 2023]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>在 Xbox One 推出之前，一系列失误让微软排名第二。不过，随着<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9ncC9wcm9kdWN0L0IwOEg3NVJUWjg_dGFnPWdkZ3QwYy1wLW8tZHMtMjAiLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6IjBhNmU2ZWRiLTRiMzYtNDI5MC1iNWU1LWE0NGFiYjYwMjRjOCJ9&amp;signature=AQAAAdCY1Ouea6Ye_E8ZBLQVFsHtK7IC6Z9AHRQ53QcLI6FU&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fgp%2Fproduct%2FB08H75RTZ8">Xbox Series X</a>和<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAVja2chGXjB4Lqvh7g-yFx643XegWlyGfH9m-TTWFYyP&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fgp%2Fproduct%2FB08G9J44ZN%2F">S</a>的推出，微软在竞争中处于有利地位。两者都是价格合理、规格齐全的游戏机，拥有跨越二十年的庞大游戏库。</p><p>微软的游戏机策略是独一无二的。拥有 7 年旧 Xbox One 的用户可以与全新 Xbox Series X 的所有者访问几乎相同的游戏库。这使得为各种游戏机维护有意义的不同列表变得困难 - 至少目前如此。不过，尽管下一代独占游戏可能很少见，据报道，PS4 的销量比 Xbox One 的销量高出二比一，但仍有很多游戏玩家根本没有体验过微软自 2017 年中期以来所提供的大部分内容。 10 年代。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>正是怀着这样的心态，我们制定了这份清单：在长期停用 Microsoft 游戏机后，我们会向今天拿起 Xbox 的人推荐哪些游戏（无论是 Series X、Series S、One X 还是 One S）？</p><p>这个列表混合了微软游戏机独有的游戏和在 Xbox 上玩得最好的跨平台游戏。我们已尽力解释 Microsoft 系统在适当的情况下带来的好处。哦，虽然我们知道有些人可能讨厌订阅服务，但绝对值得考虑<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy54Ym94LmNvbS9lbi11cy9nYW1lcy9zdG9yZS94Ym94LWdhbWUtcGFzcy11bHRpbWF0ZS9jZnE3dHRjMGtoczA_IiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiIwYTZlNmVkYi00YjM2LTQyOTAtYjVlNS1hNDRhYmI2MDI0YzgifQ&amp;signature=AQAAATA7cFPYXyTkpJeNab6R9hJfA-cPdcZE-1KJNU5fwe8R&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.xbox.com%2Fen-us%2Fgames%2Fstore%2Fxbox-game-pass-ultimate%2Fcfq7ttc0khs0%3F">Game Pass Ultimate</a> ，它允许您按月付费玩此列表中的许多游戏。</p><h2>死亡循环</h2><p><core-commerce id="ba2699a68b574aebbfe9832c3d0a725c" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> <em>《Deathloop》</em> （来自《耻辱》系列的工作室）很容易解释：你被困在不断重演的一天中。如果你死了，你就会回到早晨，再次重复这一天。如果你坚持到一天结束，你仍然会重复一遍。柯尔特必须通过有效地谋杀七个主角来“打破循环”，因为他们永远不会同时出现在同一个地方。它还时尚、方便且有趣。</p><p>当你试图摆脱这个时间异常时，你也会被另一位岛上居民朱莉安娜追捕，她和你一样，能够记住每个循环中发生的一切。她还会阻止你逃离某个区域，并且通常会干扰你逃离时间循环的计划。 （在线多人游戏也很容易让人上瘾，角色互换。你扮演朱莉安娜，追捕柯尔特并挫败他的谋杀计划。）</p><p>当你一次又一次地穿过这些区域时，你将为自己装备增加超自然力量的石板，以及更强大的武器和饰品，以嵌入枪支和你自己中。通过这个，你可以定制你的游戏风格或以最好的方式装备自己，以在朱莉安娜的帮助下生存并完成暗杀。每个时期和区域都会奖励重复探索，包括秘密枪支、与 NPC 的隐藏对话以及大量的世界建设知识等您亲自发现。</p><p> 《死亡循环》最初是 PlayStation 限时独占游戏，于 2022 年 9 月登陆 Xbox。</p><h2>守望先锋2 </h2><p><core-commerce id="3822b786d9ad4315834487174a8c9dbe" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p>尽管暴雪这次改善了新玩家的入门通道，<em>但《守望先锋 2》</em>仍然有一个陡峭的学习曲线。不过，坚持下去，你就会沉迷于也许是最好的团队射击游戏中。 <em>《守望先锋 2》</em>的目标看似简单——站在目标上或目标附近，让其他队伍远离目标足够长的时间才能获胜。实际情况要复杂得多。对于未经训练的人来说，比赛可能看起来五彩斑斓的混乱，但<em>《守望先锋 2》</em>的目标看似简单——站在目标上或目标附近，让对方远离对手足够长的时间以获得胜利。</p><p>实际情况要复杂得多。暴雪将每支队伍的玩家人数从六人减少到五人。与原版<em>《守望先锋》</em>相比，再加上全面的角色调整，游戏节奏更快、更有趣。虽然更加强调个人影响，但你仍然需要与队友良好合作才能获得胜利。</p><p>现在拥有超过 30 名英雄，每个英雄都拥有独特的能力和游戏风格，您一定会找到一些可以与您产生共鸣的<em>《守望先锋 2》</em>角色。第一批新英雄都玩起来很刺激。还有许多很棒的（尽管通常相当昂贵）新皮肤可供搭配。得益于暴雪标志性的打磨水平，这款游戏的外观和声音也非常棒。至少在你弄清楚如何玩<em>《守望先锋 2》</em>之前，你会惊叹它的精美外观。</p><h2>埃尔登之戒</h2><p><core-commerce id="" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p>你认为这份名单不会包括<a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAY-rc5BHiScd9EazPcIS1hbKT5FMEEvNJdS1NGHDyK8W&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FElden-Ring-Xbox-One%2Fdp%2FB07SMBNTSJ%2F" class="rapid-with-clickid"><em>《Elden Ring》</em></a>吗？ FromSoftware 最新的动作角色扮演游戏有很多优点，但这款游戏最令人印象深刻的是，尽管规模庞大，但它的手工制作感觉却十分出色。 <em>《Elden Ring》</em>虽然很大，但绝对不会让人觉得它在浪费你的时间。离得很远; FromSoftware 创造了一个丰富的开放世界，每个角落都有令人惊讶、令人愉快或完全可怕的东西。我永远不会忘记我发现一个箱子，将我的角色传送到一个充满可怕怪物的洞穴的那一刻。 <em>《埃尔登环》</em>充满了此类发现。</p><p>如果你担心<em>《Elden Ring》的</em>难度会碰壁，不用担心。当然，它可能很难，但它也是 From 迄今为止最容易上手的游戏。如果您发现战斗过于痛苦，请选择法师建造并从远处轰炸敌人。如果一切都失败了，探索<em>《Elden Ring》</em>世界的奖励之一就是经验，你可以用这些经验来让你的角色变得更强大。</p><h2>控制</h2><p><core-commerce id="9b0646edf9c04eb7ad8836e9a3bdd16e" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p>以<em>《心灵杀手》</em>中怪异的<em>《双峰》</em>叙事为例，将其与<em>《量子破碎</em>》的疯狂力量和枪战结合在一起，你就获得了<a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9kcC9CMDhTWjFGNUZCP3RhZz1nZGd0MGMtcC1vLWRzLTIwIiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiIwYTZlNmVkYi00YjM2LTQyOTAtYjVlNS1hNDRhYmI2MDI0YzgifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAb-mT1O2eoop_v7mVo5v6CzIKruanvg2dh0vXqu3y2Tg&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB08SZ1F5FB"><em>《控制》</em></a> 。扮演一名寻找失踪兄弟的女人，你很快就会发现现实与幻想之间只有一线之隔。对于任何从小就喜欢<em>《X 档案》</em>和超自然现象的人来说，这都是一种猫薄荷。这也是工作室在创意高度上努力的一个典型例子，完善和发展了过去十年主导游戏的开放世界公式。</p><p>对上一代 Xbox 的<em>控制效果</em>好坏参半，One S 稍显吃力，但 One X 在保真度和流畅度方面远远超过 PS4 Pro。随着下一代游戏机的推出，“终极版”出现了，它为游戏机玩家带来了 PC 游戏玩家所享受的光线追踪和更高的帧速率。虽然您只能作为下一代所有者获得这些好处，但它还包括所有已发布的 DLC，并且是我们建议购买的版本，即使您不打算立即升级。</p><h2>死角</h2><p><core-commerce id="441df37818684f368bcb28e8d55f191c" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p>这<em>&nbsp;</em> <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAeU95UrikI-RHeTi2DJOem6eEbmfry7zmmZwhGElkGXs&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FDead-Space-Xbox-X%2Fdp%2FB0BGW86RBN%3Fth%3D1" class="rapid-with-clickid"><em>《死亡空间》重制版</em></a>感觉就像来自凶残的死灵的温暖、多汁的拥抱，我们的意思是尽可能以最好的方式。 <em>《死亡空间》</em>的<a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/dead-space-remake-playstation-5-review-160019905.html">2023 版</a>对 2008 年原版游戏的机制进行了改进，并且没有添加任何不必要的现代臃肿内容。重制版具有完整的配音、新的谜题和扩展的故事情节，并引入了零重力能力，使主角艾萨克·克拉克能够以一种超令人满意的方式飞过游戏的各个部分。</p><p>这些新增内容都没有超越游戏的核心循环：<em>停滞、射击、踩踏</em>。艾萨克获得了暂时冻结敌人的能力，并且拿起了各种武器，但他从未感到被压倒；他总是处于危险之中。残缺不全的尸体怪物突然出现在空间站狭窄的走廊里，从阴影中叉腰向艾萨克冲锋，乞求被击落。第一部<em>《死亡空间》</em>普及了爆头并不重要的理念，而重制版也秉承了这一理念，但其战斗节奏仍然让人感觉新鲜。</p><p> 2023 版<em>《死亡空间》</em>证明创新的游戏设计是永恒的（等离子切割机也是如此）。</p><h2>光环：无限</h2><p><core-commerce id="f2a6ca46edb7499089e78b6b7aa31a41" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p>士官长的最新冒险可能在叙述上没有多大意义，但玩起来确实很有趣。经过 343 Industries 过去十年的努力， <a data-i13n="cpos:8;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9IYWxvLUluZmluaXRlLVhib3gtT25lLVN0YW5kYXJkL2RwL0IwN1NMNllZQlc_dGFnPWdkZ3QwYy1wLW8tZHMtMjAiLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6IjBhNmU2ZWRiLTRiMzYtNDI5MC1iNWU1LWE0NGFiYjYwMjRjOCJ9&amp;signature=AQAAAYYvislHANh4z4ZvZjJJxbVtnDXilb8DXfUkFCNI6YBZ&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FHalo-Infinite-Xbox-One-Standard%2Fdp%2FB07SL6YYBW"><em>《光环：无限》</em></a>成功地为微软的旗舰系列注入了新的生命，同时也忠于粉丝喜爱的元素。主要战役比以往更加开放，同时还通过值得信赖的抓钩为您提供了新的行动自由。多人游戏模式非常容易让人上瘾（尽管 343 仍然需要加快体验进程），有大量的地图和游戏模式可以防止事情变得过于陈旧。唯一阻碍它伟大的是它令人困惑和脱节的故事，但 Xbox 粉丝现在在大型独占游戏方面并没有太多选择。</p><h2>极限竞速地平线 5 </h2><p><core-commerce id="6fb0108a18314040989918e498d7e890" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:9;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAU0yzKlrsheJOfWA1l8p0TFSvflXUxXjwv8p8r3gYqNN&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FForza-Horizon-Standard-Xbox-One-X%2Fdp%2FB097MGZ7MY"><em>极限竞速地平线 5</em></a> <em>&nbsp;</em>这是一款极其有深度和复​​杂的赛车游戏，几乎任何人都可以轻松上手并玩。游戏中有数百辆汽车，您可以无休止地调整它们以适应您的驾驶风格，数十条赛道遍布墨西哥美丽的虚构角落。如果你提高难度，一个错误就会毁掉你的整个比赛，而在线竞争也同样激烈。</p><p>但如果您是赛车游戏新手， <em>《极限竞速：地平线 5》</em>在帮助您上手和运行方面表现出色。游戏的介绍可以让您快速了解您将遇到的四种主要比赛类型（街头赛车、越野赛等），并且诸如倒带按钮之类的功能意味着您可以快速消除错误，如果您尝试并转弯太快而无需重新开始跑步。很简单， <em>《极限竞速：地平线 5》</em>是一款精美且有趣的游戏，几乎适合任何技能水平。开始并参加几场比赛并继续你的一天是很容易的，或者你可以投入几个小时试图成为你可能成为的最好的车手。</p><h2>齿轮5 </h2><p><core-commerce id="927d5f351d414152980e31bb527bbbbc" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:10;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAb2XnfHobrWv0cDvjyMrn9_lxbM-mgMUtdIVJprVNais&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FGears-War-Game-Year-Digital%2Fdp%2FB08TS5X4N7"><em>《战争机器 5》</em></a>尝试了很多事情，但并没有全部成功。不过，如果您是《战争机器》粉丝，这里有很多值得您喜爱的内容。 The cover-shooter gameplay the series helped pioneer feels great, and the campaign, while not narratively ambitious, is well-paced and full of bombastic set pieces to keep you interested. As they stand, the various multiplayer modes are not great, but <em>Gears 5</em> is worth it for the campaign alone.</p><p> It&#39;s also a true graphical showcase, among the best-looking console games around. Microsoft did a great job optimizing for all platforms and use-cases, with high-resolution and ultra-high (up to 120fps on series consoles) frame rates.</p><h2> Nier: Automata </h2><p><core-commerce id="11f5c26099504e87a84367326ec3856d" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> It took more than a while to get here, but <a data-i13n="cpos:11;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:GameStop;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=ffe106af-8248-4af3-9098-a2d4fd637766&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=GameStop&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAX9W98Q0NTHEAWeBajzQBwNuwCZ1SKPDpIaD8BYL-zoM&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gamestop.com%2Fvideo-games%2Fproducts%2Fnier-automata---become-as-gods-edition%2F177795.html%3F"><em>Nier: Automata</em></a> finally arrived on Xbox One in the summer of 2018. And boy, was it worth the almost-18-month wait. Nier takes the razor-sharp combat of a Platinum Games title and puts it in a world crafted by everyone&#39;s favorite weirdo, Yoko Taro. Don&#39;t worry, you can mostly just run, gun and slash your way through the game, but as you finish, and finish and finish this one, you&#39;ll find yourself pulled into a truly special narrative, one that&#39;s never been done before and will probably never be done again. It&#39;s an unmissable experience, and one that feels all the more unique on Xbox, which has never had the best levels of support from Japanese developers.</p><p> On Xbox One X and Series X, you effectively have the best version of Nier: Automata available, short of a <a data-i13n="cpos:12;pos:1" href="https://steamcommunity.com/groups/SpecialK_Mods/discussions/3/1334600128973500691/">fan-patched</a> PC game. On Series S and One S... not so much, but you do at least get consistent framerates on the Series S and a passable experience on the One S.</p><h2> Ori and the Blind Forest </h2><p><core-commerce id="313443725dac4ee688d52a5a91e2fb39" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> Arriving at a time when &quot;Gears Halo Forza&quot; seemed to be the beginning, middle and end of Microsoft&#39;s publishing plans, <a data-i13n="cpos:13;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAVfTOXgeVH-KtGSKk3-IKOPfNlTEvwQjDHoEfrKOVEgq&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FOri-Blind-Forest-Definitive-Xbox-One%2Fdp%2FB01DCA8SF8"><em>Ori and the Blind Forest</em></a> was a triumph. It&#39;s a confident mash of the pixel-perfect platforming popularized by <em>Super Meat Boy</em> , and the rich, unfolding worlds of Metroidvania games. You&#39;ll die hundreds of times exploring the titular forest, unlocking skills that allow you to reach new areas. It looks and sounds great — like, Disney great — and its story, while fairly secondary to the experience, is interesting. Ori might not do much to push the boundaries of its genres, but everything it does, it does so right. Its sequel, <a data-i13n="cpos:14;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAfTE7WPzcM9M1leeu2EaffZRkeF-CWIxXNuSuGgLlwuu&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FOri-Will-Wisps-Xbox-One%2Fdp%2FB07DJRPZWY"><em>Ori and the Will of the Wisps</em></a> , is very much “more of everything,” so if you like <em>Blind Forest</em> , it&#39;s well worth checking out too.</p><h2> <strong>Pentiment</strong> </h2><p><core-commerce id="edc1d028640f45ab9e1faedd1ab7e3d9" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;cpos:15;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAATMAEflWj7xnd6hMP5TOT5C8-YIcYTo9jpcspo862H8F&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FPentiment-Xbox-Windows-Digital-Code%2Fdp%2FB0BHV2QTK4%2F" class="rapid-with-clickid"><em>Pentiment</em></a> <em>&nbsp;</em> is a 2D-adventure-meets-visual-novel set in 16th-century Bavaria. You play as Andreas Maler, a young artist from a well-to-do family who gets caught up in a murder mystery while trying to complete his masterpiece. The game itself hinges on its artwork and writing. Both are remarkable: The former is like a medieval manuscript brought to life, while the latter is at once warm and biting, but always in complete control of what it&#39;s trying to say. What starts as a seemingly straightforward whodunit turns into a sweeping, soulful meditation on the nature of history, power, community and truth itself. Time and again, it subverts the “your choices matter!” promise video games have long tried (and mostly failed) to fulfill. You don&#39;t expect one of Microsoft&#39;s best first-party Xbox games to be a riff on Umberto Eco&#39;s <em>The Name of the Rose</em> , but, well, here we are.</p><h2> <strong>Hi-Fi Rush</strong> </h2><p><core-commerce id="22f4a55e9d914e5c87e5145c963a0c21" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;cpos:16;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAcWLvbV1jxMYYTNzEZEDIIPVLEYVZl7UT8CSGlmew56L&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FHi-Fi-RUSH-Deluxe-Xbox-Digital%2Fdp%2FB0BWH8DKZ2%3Fth%3D1" class="rapid-with-clickid"><em>Hi-Fi Rush</em></a> is a hack-and-slash action game built entirely around its soundtrack. You can move and jump freely, but all of your steps and attacks are timed to the beat of the backing music. If you time your moves right <em>on</em> the beat, you can do more damage and pull off combos. Everything else in the world pulsates and takes action to the same rhythm, from enemy attacks to lights flashing in the background.</p><p> Is this revolutionary? Not really. Every hack-and-slasher has a sense of performance and musicality to it; <em>Hi-Fi Rush</em> just makes the subtext explicit. It&#39;s <em>Devil May Cry</em> on a metronome. But it&#39;s fun. Ripping through a room of goons is satisfying in most video games; ripping through them entirely in rhythm, with each dodge and final blow punctuated by a beat, is even more so. It helps that the soundtrack is actually good and that the combat system never punishes you <em>too</em> hard for button mashing in a panic. It also helps that the tone is that of a cel-shaded Saturday morning cartoon, starring a lovable doofus named Chai as he takes on a comically evil megacorp. <em>Hi-Fi Rush</em> has issues – its stages can drag, for one – but it plays like a passion project from the PS3/Xbox 360 era. It has ideas, and its main concern is being a good time.</p><h2>荒野大镖客：救赎 2 </h2><p><core-commerce id="e4c78b23150048dda39e64ce734e96af" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:17;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAATibTCIXYz2C1jYubXuCBIXn0nb7Q1Ez7omtNIcEpnPC&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FRed-Dead-Redemption-2-Xbox-One%2Fdp%2FB01MAYC1CJ"><em>Red Dead Redemption 2</em></a> is the kind of game no one but Rockstar, the team behind the GTA series, could make. Only when a studio is this successful can it pour millions of dollars and development hours into a game. Rockstar&#39;s simulation of a crumbling frontier world is enthralling and serves as a perfect backdrop to an uncharacteristically measured story. While the studio&#39;s gameplay may not have moved massively forward, the writing and characters of RDR2 will stay with you.</p><p> While Rockstar hasn&#39;t deemed fit to properly upgrade <em>Red Dead Redemption 2</em> for the next-gen yet, Series X owners will at least benefit from the best last-gen (Xbox One X) experience with the addition of improved loading times. The Series S, on the other hand, gets the One S version, but with an improved 30 fps lock and swifter loading.</p><h2>生化危机村庄</h2><p><core-commerce id="7c30a7a48013413cbce2e0e2ef61437b" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:18;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9SZXNpZGVudC1FdmlsLVZpbGxhZ2UtWGJveC1YLVN0YW5kYXJkL2RwL0IwOTQ3ODlZUkg_dGFnPWdkZ3QwYy1wLW8tZHMtMjAiLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6IjBhNmU2ZWRiLTRiMzYtNDI5MC1iNWU1LWE0NGFiYjYwMjRjOCJ9&amp;signature=AQAAAfJmstwVEyn8HZv9ZyhLJzF1iav2cmw3ckOJL5JBjx2P&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FResident-Evil-Village-Xbox-X-Standard%2Fdp%2FB094789YRH"><em>Resident Evil Village</em></a> is delightful. It&#39;s a gothic fairy tale masquerading as a survival-horror game, and while this represents a fresh vibe for the franchise, it&#39;s not an unwelcome evolution. The characters and enemies in Village are full of life — even when they&#39;re decidedly undead — and Capcom has put a delicious twist on the idea of vampires, werewolves, sea creatures, giants and creepy dolls. The game retains its horror, puzzle and action roots, and it has Umbrella Corporation&#39;s fingerprints all over it. It simply feels like developers had fun with this one, and so will you.</p><p> A word of caution before you run to buy it, though: This game doesn&#39;t play great on every Xbox. On Series X, things are great: There&#39;s the option to turn on ray-tracing with the occasional frame rate issue, or to keep it off and have perfect 4K/60 presentation. With the Series S, while there is a ray-tracing mode, it&#39;s almost unplayable. With ray-tracing off, the Series S does a decent job, though. The One X&#39;s 1080p/60 mode is also fantastic, although its quality mode feels very juddery. If you own a base Xbox One or One S, though, there&#39;s really no mode that actually feels enjoyable to play.</p><h2> Sekiro: Shadows Die Twice </h2><p><core-commerce id="1c855dbac578431e98cd9742e800faf3" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:19;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9TZWtpcm8tU2hhZG93cy1Ud2ljZS1EaWdpdGFsLVN0YW5kYXJkL2RwL0IwN1ozWEw0UVA_dGFnPWdkZ3QwYy1wLW8tZHMtMjAiLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6IjBhNmU2ZWRiLTRiMzYtNDI5MC1iNWU1LWE0NGFiYjYwMjRjOCJ9&amp;signature=AQAAAWqL_CsEamZZyAf5YVE3vj3hqm-qVYtRphiN8Dd_IvgE&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FSekiro-Shadows-Twice-Digital-Standard%2Fdp%2FB07Z3XL4QP"><em>Sekiro: Shadows Die Twice</em></a> isn&#39;t just another Dark Souls game. FromSoftware&#39;s samurai adventure is a departure from that well-established formula, replacing slow, weighty combat and gothic despair for stealth, grappling hooks and swift swordplay. Oh, and while it&#39;s still a difficult game, it&#39;s a lot more accessible than Souls games — you can even pause it! The result of all these changes is something that&#39;s still instantly recognizable as a FromSoftware title, but it&#39;s its own thing, and it&#39;s very good.</p><p> This is one game that&#39;s really not had a lot of love from its developer or publisher, as, despite the fact next-gen consoles should be easily able to run this game at 60 fps, the Series S is locked to an inconsistently paced 30 fps, while the Series X doesn&#39;t quite hold to 60 either. With that said, it&#39;s more than playable.</p><h2> Lost Judgment </h2><p><core-commerce id="b034ca2c0dd64c65bd41eae2fb8a78c5" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> This is private eye Takayuki Yagami&#39;s <a data-i13n="cpos:20;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:GameStop;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=ffe106af-8248-4af3-9098-a2d4fd637766&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=GameStop&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAbUclKxTgGXlHAtfLZeZ1icGRYZts0EQCyjo_Nj7NVIJ&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gamestop.com%2Fvideo-games%2Fproducts%2Flost-judgment---xbox-series-x%2F291075.html%3F">second adventure</a> ; a spin-off of Sega&#39;s popular, pulpy and convoluted Yakuza saga. He lives in the same Kamurocho area, the same yakuza gangs roam the streets, and there&#39;s the very occasional crossover of side-story characters and, well, weirdos. But instead of punching punks in the face in the name of justice or honor, which was the style of Yakuza <em>&nbsp;</em> protagonist Kazuya Kiryu, Yagami fights with the power of his lawyer badge, drone evidence and… sometimes (read: often) he kicks the bad guys in the face.</p><p> The sequel skates even closer to some sort of serialized TV drama, punctuated by fights, chases and melodrama. For anyone that&#39;s played the series before, it treads familiar ground, but with a more serious (realistic) story that centers on bullying and suicide problems in Japanese high schools, which is tied into myriad plots encompassing the legal system, politics and organized crime.</p><p> Yagami has multiple fighting styles to master, while there are love interests, batting cages, mahjong, skate parks and more activities to sink even more hours into. On the PS5, <em>Lost Judgment</em> looks great. Fights are fluid and the recreated areas in Tokyo and Yokohama are usually full of pedestrians, stores and points of interest. While <em>Yakuza Like a Drago</em> n takes the franchise in a new (turn-based, more ridiculous) direction, <em>Lost Judgment</em> retains the brawling playstyle of the Yakuza series, with a new hero who has, eventually, charmed us.</p><h2> Xbox Game Pass Ultimate </h2><p><core-commerce id="137f22a6da5f44dfab7ac111345e22b4" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> We already mentioned this one but it&#39;s difficult to overemphasize how good a deal <a data-i13n="cpos:21;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9YYm94LUdhbWUtUGFzcy1VbHRpbWF0ZS1NZW1iZXJzaGlwL2RwL0IwN1RGUDdKRkg_dGFnPWdkZ3QwYy1wLW8tZHMtMjAiLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6IjBhNmU2ZWRiLTRiMzYtNDI5MC1iNWU1LWE0NGFiYjYwMjRjOCJ9&amp;signature=AQAAAbIx13ZjEsaaH0nMgLx2YYuLdPxuDIBtEKFdsJ-lNDuE&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FXbox-Game-Pass-Ultimate-Membership%2Fdp%2FB07TFP7JFH">Game Pass</a> is for Xbox owners. For $15 a month you get access to a shifting and growing library of games. The company does a good job explaining what games are coming and going in advance, so you won&#39;t get caught out by a game disappearing from the subscription service just as you&#39;re reaching a final boss. There are 11 games mentioned in this guide, and seven of them are currently available with Game Pass. The full library is broad, and, while Microsoft&#39;s cloud service is still just in beta, you&#39;ll have access to many of the games on your tablet, phone or browser through xCloud at no extra fee.</p> This article originally appeared on Engadget at https://www.engadget.com/best-xbox-games-140022399.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/best-xbox-games-140022399.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 0a6e6edb-4b36-4290-b5e5-a44abb6024c8</guid><dc:creator> Engadget</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher> Engadget</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder> Engadget</dc:rightsholder><pubDate> Wed, 28 Jun 2023 13:52:15 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1687963081</ingested><modified> 2023-06-28T14:38:13+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Consumer Discretionary]]></category><category><![CDATA[Media]]></category><category><![CDATA[Video Games]]></category><category><![CDATA[Arts & Entertainment]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Engadget]]></category><media:content height="1240" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2020-11/1a78db70-1d1c-11eb-8f7e-21a8e3cff5ce" width="2000"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="1240" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2020-11/1a78db70-1d1c-11eb-8f7e-21a8e3cff5ce" width="2000"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Aaron Souppouris / Engadget]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[Microsoft's new Series X console and its accessories.]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Xbox Series X]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Kia EV9 first drive: Adding a third row to the EV market]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p> It makes sense that a majority of EVs are crossovers. It&#39;s a market segment that does well. Sure, they&#39;re essentially raised hatchbacks, but they offer enough cargo space and seating for a couple or small family. On the other hand, if you have a large brood or need to transport a lot of supplies, gear, or groceries, the electrification of a three-row vehicle has been slow. Fortunately, the Kia EV9 is here with seating for up to seven and a cavernous cargo space.</p><p> We had a chance to take the Korean-spec EV9 for a first drive in Korea and while the suspension was a bit softer than what we&#39;re used to in the United States and there&#39;s a good chance that the acceleration will be tweaked to deliver more zip, it delivered the electric vehicle experience we expect from the automaker.</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p> With a targeted range of up to 300 miles and DC fast charging that Kia says will take the 99.8kWh capacity battery from 10 percent to 80 percent in about 24 minutes, the automaker has something that should appeal to families looking for a road trip SUV. For more details on the EV9 and how it fared on the road, check out the video below. </p><div id="0cc9bbc497f5417b88547aa920242625"><iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/tTdeESJjses?rel=0" style="top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;position:absolute;border:0;" allowfullscreen="" scrolling="no"></iframe></div><p></p> This article originally appeared on Engadget at https://www.engadget.com/kia-ev9-first-drive-adding-a-third-row-to-the-ev-market-134533948.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/kia-ev9-first-drive-adding-a-third-row-to-the-ev-market-134533948.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> a11e9bfd-da1a-478e-a6a6-238ef303fe34</guid><dc:creator> Roberto Baldwin</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher> Engadget</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder> Engadget</dc:rightsholder><pubDate> Wed, 28 Jun 2023 13:45:33 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1687963003</ingested><modified> 2023-06-28T14:36:46+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Automotive Industry]]></category><category><![CDATA[Autos]]></category><category><![CDATA[Transportation]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Roberto Baldwin]]></category><media:content height="1667" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/3daa97e0-15b8-11ee-add3-8bec3aa335ec" width="2500"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="1667" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/3daa97e0-15b8-11ee-add3-8bec3aa335ec" width="2500"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Roberto Baldwin for Engadget]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[Kia EV9]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Kia EV9]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Shokz OpenFit delivers open-ear audio without bone conduction]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p> The team at Shokz has made a name for itself in the bone conduction headset market over the past several years and they&#39;ve decided to change things up a bit this time around. Today, the company announced its newest headphones and while it&#39;s still an open-ear design, it&#39;s not bone conduction. The <a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://shokz.com/products/openfit">Shokz OpenFit</a> Bluetooth earbuds ($179.95) are called “air conduction” in a twist on the brand&#39;s bone conduction brethren. Like many open-ear buds before them, they are positioned just outside of your ear with an over-the-ear hook to keep them in place. As a lifestyle headset, they work well, keeping your hearing open (to some degree), staying in place when you move about and are easy to wear for long periods of time.</p><p> The OpenFit seems to bridge the gap between the audio quality of in-ear buds and the situational awareness of bone conduction. They definitely deliver better audio (including bass) than the bone conduction models and still let you hear some of what&#39;s going on around you. Sure, they&#39;re not quite a replacement for in-ear buds, but that wasn&#39;t really the goal. All that said, I found that they can be hit or miss with dance music, since there&#39;s an issue with handling hard hits on <em>some</em> low frequency sounds.</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p> Externally, these start off on the same page as most similarly designed earbuds. They come with a charging case, fit over your ear with dolphin arc hooks and to the passer-by, won&#39;t appear unusual. They&#39;re matte black (or beige), made with a soft silicone exterior and feel very lightweight. It&#39;s not outlandish to say you <em>could</em> forget you&#39;re wearing them. They&#39;re definitely lighter and more comfortable than the single-unit bone conduction models Shokz sells, and it&#39;s nice not to have a band around the back. </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/6d1a7880-11dd-11ee-b7e5-058e19397e90" style="height:1200px;" alt="Close-up images of the Shokz OpenFit open-ear buds in grey." data-uuid="805d14e4-8082-3a25-b958-6ca537e6e817"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit"> Photo by Jon Turi / Engadget</div></figure><p> Like many earbuds, Shokz has graciously included touch controls including double-tap and long-press interactions. They respond well to your touches and taps, plus you can customize the functionality in the iOS or Android apps, although the latter won&#39;t be ready at launch. You can use a single bud if you want and keep the other inside the charging case without issue, although you will be limited to that choice&#39;s touch-control setting.</p><p> While Shokz&#39;s previous offerings were primarily geared toward fitness (the OpenComm series aside), the OpenFit is pitched as more of a lifestyle product. They&#39;re something you can wear as you go about your day without leaning on digital transparency modes to hear the world. The earbuds themselves are IP54 rated so you&#39;re good if you <em>do</em> work out in them, but the charging case is not. You&#39;ll want to try to remember to wipe them off before stowing them to keep everything in good working order.</p><p> The OpenFit and its ear hook seem to work well at keeping them in place, too. I wouldn&#39;t worry about them falling off if you&#39;re running around, lifting weights, stretching or doing physical activities. It may seem like they could, since they&#39;re not wedged into your ear, but so far I&#39;ve found them to stay put. </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/6d28a950-11dd-11ee-afad-f5c82c457377" style="height:1200px;" alt="Close-up images of the Shokz OpenFit open-ear buds in grey being worn by someone seen in profile." data-uuid="4dc9614a-6846-341c-8bf1-32a7e345b36a"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit"> Photo by Jon Turi / Engadget</div></figure><p> As for specs, the Shokz OpenFit earbuds run Bluetooth 5.2, have a frequency response of 50Hz - 16kHz, support AAC and SBC codecs and there are 18 x 11mm customized dynamic drivers inside for the output. The battery life of the buds are rated at up to 7 hours of listening on a charge, with the case said to expand that up to 28 hours of playback. As with previous Shokz headsets, you get an hour&#39;s worth of juice with just 5-minutes of charging. That&#39;s great if you notice a low charge before heading out on a run with just OpenFit and a smartwatch or phone.</p><p> One of the frequent issues with bone conduction headsets has been the lack of bass. Shokz came a long way towards cracking the case with their latest <a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/aftershokz-shokz-openrun-pro-bone-conduction-headphones-bass-030031419.html">OpeRun Pro</a> headset. The OpenFit aren&#39;t bone conduction, so it was easier for the company to deliver a pumped up low-end profile.</p><p> If you&#39;re a Shokz fan, you&#39;ll probably enjoy these, especially for casual daily use at lower volumes. They work well for music and spoken word, and unlike the bone conduction models you&#39;ll have better luck hearing your music if you&#39;re in a busier environment. Although, keep in mind these are still open-ear models, so your listening experience isn&#39;t totally isolated.</p><p> I&#39;ve worn these while going to the store and doing other errands. If you keep music playing at normal or low volumes, you can enjoy tunes while also listening to and conversing with cashiers and other people around you. While you <em>can</em> take phone calls with a double tap, I chose to ditch them with a long press when interacting as a courtesy. </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/6d28d060-11dd-11ee-a5ac-4d0a904d8990" style="height:1200px;" alt="Close-up images of the Shokz OpenFit open-ear buds in grey." data-uuid="e76b751f-d38a-3d9d-b209-a5097abb2ef5"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit"> Photo by Jon Turi / Engadget</div></figure><p> You can <em>&nbsp;</em> even ride your bike while wearing these and still hear what&#39;s going on around you if you&#39;re careful with the volume. Bone conduction headphones (the <a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/aftershokz-shokz-openrun-pro-bone-conduction-headphones-bass-030031419.html">Shokz OpenRun Pro</a> specifically) are a more optimized situational awareness headset though, and visibly leave both ears open in case <a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://brooklynfixedgear.com/law-and-safety/is-it-illegal-to-bike-with-headphones/">local laws</a> have restrictions.</p><p> If you&#39;re the type of person who enjoys cranking up your tunes, there are some caveats. The overall listening experience does offer rich bass, along with good mids and highs for this form factor. But if you tend to listen to dance music or hip hop, you may notice an issue with the handling of some very low-end kick drums. On some songs, mostly with hard hitting bits at low frequencies, you may notice a crunchy edge to those beats. If you get the opportunity to test them first, I&#39;d bring something along these lines to check your experience.</p><p> Listening to The Dave Brubeck Quartet&#39;s “ <a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL29wZW4uc3BvdGlmeS5jb20vdHJhY2svM2tLNjZHaldZOEVjc3hCa1NFbTQzVD9zaT03YWQ5M2I3NmEwMGE0ZGEzIiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiI5ZDJlZGM3Mi1iNzBhLTQwZTktODg2Mi0yODczNGE0MTdlNWEifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAdTr3WqTIfSgRD-Ggl9qIl_5rwx39vdNLPuNBIRQMIIA&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fopen.spotify.com%2Ftrack%2F3kK66GjWY8EcsxBkSEm43T%3Fsi%3D7ad93b76a00a4da3">Three to Get Ready</a> ” was clear and pleasant, with a natural sound and smooth basslines. The UMC&#39;s “ <a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL29wZW4uc3BvdGlmeS5jb20vdHJhY2svN0lEVDBTQUU2a09aOWlvRHZIQzJsQz9zaT04YzBkYWE2MGNkZGY0YTJiIiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiI5ZDJlZGM3Mi1iNzBhLTQwZTktODg2Mi0yODczNGE0MTdlNWEifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAeMTI2dySlUeK3Odxr_3xBXqATKwN3Nhk4a8B-6spYXE&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fopen.spotify.com%2Ftrack%2F7IDT0SAE6kOZ9ioDvHC2lC%3Fsi%3D8c0daa60cddf4a2b">Some Sepak Ill Thoughts</a> ” generally sounded good with a slight crunchiness on a specific ultra-low bassline section. Listening to both DITC&#39;s bass-heavy “ <a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL29wZW4uc3BvdGlmeS5jb20vdHJhY2svNkRseTVpTGFjQURtSkFTYWxqd01nNj9zaT1mZDUxYTVjM2QzMmY0YTYzIiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiI5ZDJlZGM3Mi1iNzBhLTQwZTktODg2Mi0yODczNGE0MTdlNWEifQ&amp;signature=AQAAATnYR3PjFp4QboxPCaIVBbkY6g6zKao8aV45Qdg6KEM2&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fopen.spotify.com%2Ftrack%2F6Dly5iLacADmJASaljwMg6%3Fsi%3Dfd51a5c3d32f4a63">Thick (Environmentally Friendly Version)</a> ” and the 4/4 techno of Ryan Elliot&#39;s “ <a data-i13n="cpos:8;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL29wZW4uc3BvdGlmeS5jb20vdHJhY2svMGRZVkRyQnpUWXdsT0FGM3E2UTVGcD9zaT1kY2U1ZjI1OWFmYjU0YzFmIiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiI5ZDJlZGM3Mi1iNzBhLTQwZTktODg2Mi0yODczNGE0MTdlNWEifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAQj9QKSl2V_CpbVHfgznYi3aYHzPYVbt3H2g1uPjkHcK&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fopen.spotify.com%2Ftrack%2F0dYVDrBzTYwlOAF3q6Q5Fp%3Fsi%3Ddce5f259afb54c1f">Fermi II</a> ” both surfaced the kick-drum crunch a bit. Radiohead&#39;s “ <a data-i13n="cpos:9;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL29wZW4uc3BvdGlmeS5jb20vdHJhY2svMDJwcE1QYmcxT3RFZEhnb1Bxb3FqdT9zaT1mODY0MDc2N2YwMzM0MjQwIiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiI5ZDJlZGM3Mi1iNzBhLTQwZTktODg2Mi0yODczNGE0MTdlNWEifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAffbVpiRrCX9c6-HtSI_T1Xzr7N9TLh9ZOO3tUtfOwps&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fopen.spotify.com%2Ftrack%2F02ppMPbg1OtEdHgoPqoqju%3Fsi%3Df8640767f0334240">Reckoner</a> ” was a pleasant listen throughout. Obviously it depends on the music and only seems noticeable on certain punchy and low frequencies. </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/2e7474e0-11de-11ee-8f63-38ce18f8dada" style="height:1200px;" alt="Screenshots of the Shokz OpenFit app settings menu." data-uuid="e9ef93a1-4acd-30d9-a1f4-019298263f9a"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit"> Photo by Jon Turi / Engadget</div></figure><p> The app that Shokz released for OpenRun Pro in 2022 will now also work with your OpenFit earbuds and it&#39;s relatively essential, since there are touch controls that you&#39;ll want to customize. The iOS version will be available at launch, with the Android version arriving at a later date. Using the app, you can select from EQ presets or create your own, customize the touch controls, control playback and view battery levels for each earbud as well as the charging case.</p><p> There are two types of touch controls available, which are double tap and press-and-hold. You can select from pre-set combinations, which seem to cover enough options to satisfy most people. They&#39;re a mix of play/pause, previous/next, voice assistant and lastly volume control (which is only available for the press-and-hold interaction).</p><p> The standard EQ preset seems to be the most common choice for most listening. Vocal and treble boost are similar, while the bass boost just increases the prevalence of low-end but not its power necessarily. Obviously you can use the custom option to find your own sweet spot. </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/6d288240-11dd-11ee-bf3b-bdece0d7376b" style="height:1200px;" alt="灰色 Shokz OpenFit 开放式耳机与充电盒的特写图片。" data-uuid="41306058-98b9-3698-b4a0-8a2c84ccb250"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit"> Photo by Jon Turi / Engadget</div></figure><p> Overall, these sound good for the form factor and Shokz fans that enjoy an open-ear experience may appreciate the move away from bone conduction for a change. For casual everyday use, the fit and audio experience is much improved, while still offering a degree of situational awareness. The issue with certain low-end frequencies and drum kicks is my only quibble with an otherwise solid listening experience.</p><p> Shokz OpenFit earbuds are available starting today at the company&#39;s <a data-i13n="cpos:10;pos:1" href="https://shokz.com/products/openfit">website</a> , as well as <a data-i13n="cpos:11;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9kcC9CMEJZU1FEV1JUP3RhZz1nZGd0MGMtcC1vLTFtYy0yMCIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiOWQyZWRjNzItYjcwYS00MGU5LTg4NjItMjg3MzRhNDE3ZTVhIn0&amp;signature=AQAAASUKDDEukymtAugpuwll0z2dkYegidmqKf-aFc1hN71J&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB0BYSQDWRT">Amazon</a> for $179.95 in both black and beige options.</p><p><core-commerce id="1c9f399f131c41b0a396c876e54c73d2" data-type="product-list"></p><p></p> This article originally appeared on Engadget at https://www.engadget.com/shokz-openfit-delivers-open-ear-audio-without-bone-conduction-130058496.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/shokz-openfit-delivers-open-ear-audio-without-bone-conduction-130058496.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 9d2edc72-b70a-40e9-8862-28734a417e5a</guid><dc:creator> Jon Turi</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher> Engadget</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder> Engadget</dc:rightsholder><pubDate> Wed, 28 Jun 2023 13:00:58 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1687960505</ingested><modified> 2023-06-28T13:55:10+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Consumer Discretionary]]></category><category><![CDATA[Technology & Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></cate